parameters: ......The safe is already open. There is nothing inside anymore...

There is a safe. ... I have no intention of touching it, let alone
opening it.

A Vajra made skillfully from junk and waste materials. It resembled
the talisman that Araka used for work.
Do you want to take the talisman?
Just when I was about to
When I touched the talisman, Araka's image flashed in my mind.

There is no doubt. This is something left behind by Araka. However...
compared to Araka's previous belongings, there are fewer readable
thoughts. It felt like my vision was obstructed by something dark and
hazy... that was the sensation.
With a hint of unease, you carefully stowed away the talisman.

When I approached out of curiosity, I found something like a jewel
lying there. It seemed to be one of the beads that were probably
connected as a rosary.

It seems to be a door leading to the fourth floor, but no matter how
much I push or pull, it won't budge. It appears to be locked.

When I inserted the key I obtained from the safe into the keyhole, the
lock easily opened. The door, although rusty, also opened easily. It's
as if I'm being invited in...

If I approach the door, it opens without even touching it... Is it
Araka's power, perhaps? Maybe Araka wants me to go outside with this
power.

I grip the doorknob and push the rusty door. Stepping into the
darkness that lies beyond.
The power is on. It seems like we can go down below.
I have a lock on the inside, but it seems like I can open it.
Do you want me to unlock it?
The power is on. It seems like we can go down below.
